elements.title: Walther von Klingen (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Minnesang poet Walther von Klingen is depicted jousting (pictured) in the Codex Manesse manuscript?

elements.title: Le Tombeau de Couperin (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that in Le Tombeau de Couperin, George Balanchine's ballet to Ravel's orchestral suite, the dancers are divided into two groups, dancing separately?

elements.title: Guy Alfred Wyon (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Guy Alfred Wyon helped discover a remedy for TNT poisoning in British shell factories in World War I?

elements.title: The Ice Age Adventures of Buck Wild (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that none of the original core Ice Age cast returned for The Ice Age Adventures of Buck Wild?

elements.title: Cyrus Prudhomme David (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the Colonial Office refused to appoint Cyrus Prudhomme David to the magistracy, considering it wrong "as a matter of policy" to appoint a second Black man to a legal post in Trinidad and Tobago?

elements.title: Journalist in Space Project (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Walter Cronkite was one of 40 finalists in NASA's Journalist in Space Project?

elements.title: Kuala Langat North Forest Reserve (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the Selangor State Executive Council degazetted most of the Kuala Langat North Forest Reserve, despite the legislative assembly having unanimously voted to preserve it?

elements.title: Sophie de Ronde (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that brewer Sophie de Ronde is allergic to most beer?
